cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the capacity scaling laws of ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to information theory and network information theory (cs.IT, cs.NI). The use of a doubly stochastic shot-noise Cox process to model the node distribution suggests a focus on stochastic processes and random networks (cs.MA, cs.SI). Finally, the analysis of different operational regimes and the development of communication strategies suggest a focus on distributed systems and algorithms (cs.DS).
